title: Symmetric Zooming: a Zooming Method for Conventional Pointing Devices
title_en: Symmetric Zooming: a Zooming Method for Conventional Pointing Devices
abstract: 本研究は画像や図、地図などの表示でズーム操作の際にズームアウト後に元の表示に戻る対称性を重視したズーミング手法を提案している。提案した手法はホイール非搭載の通常のマウスやペンといったポインティング機器でも対称性を実現することを目標とし、画面上の座標と複数の倍率（例:4倍、8倍）を用いた実装上の振る舞いを設計している。
abstract_en: This study proposes a zooming method that emphasizes symmetry when zooming so that a view returns to its original state after zooming out and back in. The proposed method aims to realize symmetry for conventional pointing devices without wheels by defining behavior based on screen coordinates and multiple magnification levels such as 4x and 8x.
positioning_summary: 本研究はズーム操作においてズームアウト後にズームインすると元の画像に戻る対称性が重要であることを指摘して対称性を重視したズーミングを位置づけている。対称性を重視したズーミングを本研究はホイール付きマウスでは容易に得られるがホイール非搭載の通常マウスやペンでは得にくい点を問題として位置づけている。
positioning_summary_en: This study positions symmetric zooming as important because a view should return to its original state after zooming out and back in. This study positions the problem by noting that wheel-equipped mice can easily achieve symmetry while conventional mice and pens without wheels have difficulty achieving that symmetry.
purpose_summary: 本研究の目的はホイール非搭載の通常のポインティング機器利用者でも対称ズーミングの恩恵を受けられるようにすることである。対称ズーミングの実現を本研究は通常のマウスやペンを対象にして目指している。
purpose_summary_en: The purpose of this study is to enable users of conventional pointing devices without wheels to benefit from symmetric zooming. This study aims to realize symmetric zooming specifically for devices such as standard mice and pens.
method_summary: 本研究は通常のマウスやペンに適した対称ズーミング手法を提案して実装上の振る舞いを設計している。提案手法は画面上の座標(x,y)や複数の倍率（例:4倍、8倍）を扱う定義を用い、本研究はホイール付きマウスと同等の対称性を目指して操作の仕組みを設計している。
method_summary_en: This study proposes a symmetric zooming method suitable for conventional mice and pens and designs its implementation behavior. The proposed method uses definitions based on screen coordinates (x,y) and multiple magnification levels such as 4x and 8x, aiming to achieve symmetry comparable to wheel-equipped mice.
evaluation_summary: 本研究はユーザ課題に基づく測定実験で提案手法の性能を評価する方法を採用して比較を行っている。提案手法はホイール付きマウスと比較する測定実験の結果でホイール付きマウスと同等の性能であることが確認されている。
evaluation_summary_en: This study evaluated the proposed method using measured experiments based on user tasks and performed comparisons in that experimental framework. The proposed method was confirmed by those user-task measurements to have performance equivalent to a wheel-equipped mouse.

Title: Symmetric Zooming: a Zooming Method for Conventional Pointing Devices
Authors: Minoru Terada, Hideto Takei
Year: 2005
Abstract: This study proposes a zooming method that emphasizes symmetry when zooming so that a view returns to its original state after zooming out and back in. The proposed method aims to realize symmetry for conventional pointing devices without wheels by defining behavior based on screen coordinates and multiple magnification levels such as 4x and 8x.
Positioning Summary: This study positions symmetric zooming as important because a view should return to its original state after zooming out and back in. This study positions the problem by noting that wheel-equipped mice can easily achieve symmetry while conventional mice and pens without wheels have difficulty achieving that symmetry.
Purpose Summary: The purpose of this study is to enable users of conventional pointing devices without wheels to benefit from symmetric zooming. This study aims to realize symmetric zooming specifically for devices such as standard mice and pens.
Method Summary: This study proposes a symmetric zooming method suitable for conventional mice and pens and designs its implementation behavior. The proposed method uses definitions based on screen coordinates (x,y) and multiple magnification levels such as 4x and 8x, aiming to achieve symmetry comparable to wheel-equipped mice.
Evaluation Summary: This study evaluated the proposed method using measured experiments based on user tasks and performed comparisons in that experimental framework. The proposed method was confirmed by those user-task measurements to have performance equivalent to a wheel-equipped mouse.
